OL,3,CFire at lithium battery factory kills
OL,4,C22 in South Korea
OL,6,FExploding lithium batteries are
OL,7,Fbelieved to be the cause of a fire
OL,8,Fthat swept through a factory in South
OL,9,FKorea that killed 22 people, many of
OL,10,Fthem migrant workers from China.
OL,12,FThe fire began after batteries
OL,13,Fexploded while workers were examining
OL,14,Fand packaging them on the second floor
OL,15,Fof the factory in Hwaseong, just south
OL,16,Fof Seoul, at around 10:30 am, fire
OL,17,Fofficials said.
OL,19,FThe dead included 18 Chinese, two
OL,20,FSouth Koreans and one Laotian, local
OL,21,Ffire official Kim Jin-young said.
